Package: facet
Title: facet: Univeriate and Multivariate Generalizability Theory with frequentist and Bayesian methods
Version: 0.0.2
Authors@R: c(
    person("George", "Michaelides", email = "g.michaelides@uea.ac.uk", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("George", "Michaelides", email = "g.michaelides@uea.ac.uk", role = c("aut")),
    person("Duncan", "Jackson", email = "duncan.jackson@kcl.ac.uk", role = "aut")
  )
Description: Conduct generalizability theory analyses using variance component
    models estimated with various methods (including ANOVA method of momnets, REML with lme4, and NUTES with brms. Provides functions for G-studies 
    (estimating variance components) and D-studies (computing generalizability 
    and dependability coefficients).
